data.title: Timberwolves Sign Tayshaun Prince
data.meta_description: Minneapolis/St. Paul – The Minnesota Timberwolves today announced the team has signed veteran forward Tayshaun Prince. Per team policy, terms of the contract were not disclosed. “We’re excited to add a veteran like Tayshaun,” said Timberwolves president of basketball operations and head coach Flip Saunders. “Having coached Tayshaun for three seasons in Detroit, I know that his experience and defensive mindset will benefit our younger players. He also has shown that he can shoot from long distance, which will help our ability to stretch the floor.”
